have a facebook conversation only using words that could be made from
the symbols of the periodic table.  (Please don't comment) I spied a
chance to ignore my wife for half-an-hour and impress her with my
chemical wit afterwards - surely it can't be difficult to create a
quick script to generate all the combinations?  Spoiler - no, it's
easy!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First challenge - getting a list of elements in a convenient format.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;http://pastebin.com/raw.php?i=CKwm136x&lt;/code&gt; - a quick google and done!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then, the script.  I've cheated here and replaced the csv-parsing with
a &lt;code&gt;set&lt;/code&gt; constructor - but I did learn about the &lt;code&gt;next&lt;/code&gt; method to
advance an iteratable (to skip the header on the CSV file).  I guess
that without more work than I can squeeze in (i.e. not capable of),
I'm not going to do better than Python's set union and intersection
methods.  Ditto for generating the permutations.&lt;/p&gt;
